FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
An increase from FY2026 to FY2027 of $9.222 million is requested, with the majority allocated to advancing
the primary development of the MDA solution. This funding will support the continuation of platform, secure
mission control element and ground control station integrations, the initiation of laboratory activities, and
planning for flight demonstrations to validate maritime detection, tracking, and data fusion performance. Funding
supports completion of system prototype, environmental validation, and airworthiness certification, cybersecurity
accreditation, and developmental test and operational assessment. This budget increase also provides for spiral
capability development to enhance and mature technology towards full operational capability, including the use
of Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning to stay ahead of threats and for DAAS system design updates to
support FAA safety certification.
