E. Acquisition Strategy
FAMM is one of the initial Modular Weapon Series (M-Series) family of weapons designed with open and common hardware and software interface standards to
increase acquisition agility, lower costs of weapon development and modification, and be rapidly upgradeable to respond to adversary actions. FAMM weapons are
designed for affordable manufacturability, with innovative concepts to support scaleability to high production rates. Example manufacturing concepts are distributed/
franchised production across suppliers/nodes (to include coalition partners), use of commonly available manufacturing equipment and processes to support access to
more production facilities, and Industry 4.0 techniques such as additive manufacturing and automation.

 FAMM will execute an incremental approach to development, integration, testing, production and fielding that ensures each increment proves out feasibility, sets
 the conditions for the next increment, and includes on-ramps to leverage the latest commercial innovations. By design, the frequent iterative increments serve as
 checkpoints to evaluate investment, technology risk, affordability and manufacturability. The resulting FAMM development and production pipeline will be cost- effective,
 scalable, and responsive to a range of strategic scenarios.




