       Change Summary Explanation
       In FY 2025, a decrease of $6.510 million in reprogramming was due to realignment of funds to support autonomous collaborative platforms studies (PE
       0603680F), specialty materials (PE 0603680F), cyber effects in contested environments (PE 0603788F), AI/ML computing at the edge (PE 0603788F), and
       software defined radio (PE 0603788F).

       In FY 2025, a decrease of $5.735 million in Other Adjustments was due to realignment of funds to PE 0602212F, Defense Laboratories R&D Projects, to
       implement the Department of War (DoW) Funding Laboratory Enhancements Across Four Categories (FLEX-4) authority under 10 U.S.C Section 4123.

       The FY 2026 President's Budget submittal did not reflect FY 2027 through FY 2030 funding. Therefore, an explanation of the change between the two budget
       positions for FY 2027 cannot be made in a relevant manner.

