C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                   FY 2025     FY 2026       FY 2027
Title: ABADS Counter-small Unmanned Aircraft Systems (C-sUAS)                                                                            15.188       9.917        29.199
Description: The ABADS C-sUAS program will continue to defend against emerging and growing airborne threats. This program
protects strategic assets vital to national security while bedded down and while on the move. This program will continue to counter
emerging threats posed by advancements in enemy employment tactics and commercially available technology.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Update Medusa Command and Control (C2) software furthering interoperability and incorporation within the Advanced Battle
Management System (ABMS) architecture (e.g., Unified Data Library).
- Upgrade electronic warfare, including but not limited to new sensor and effector components, and new Ninja skills leveraging full
Ninja capability within Medusa C2 and other C2 systems.
- Continue efforts in alignment with the DoW's Joint Interagency Task Force (JIATF) 401.
- Evaluate new capabilities.
- Develop and test C2 capabilities, via planned incremental software sprints, annual software upgrades.

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                       FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
- Ensure cyber security requirements are developed and incorporated in all new system changes.
- Support oversight, management, and execution of JIATF funded development efforts.
- Conduct studies, analysis, and evaluations of threats and capability gaps to refine and update requirements enabling upgraded
and improved capabilities.
- Initiate and continue contractor testing of developed updates.
- Integrate initial kinetic effectors for evaluation for broader DAF employment to include low collateral effects intercept (LCEI)
capabilities and other kinetic solutions such as Advanced Precision Kill Weapon System (APKWS).
- Integrate capabilities on expeditionary systems.
- Develop NCR COP technical solutions to include joint interoperability of Counter-small Unmanned Aircraft Systems (C-sUAS)
sensors, development of correlation and fusion process, and developing cyber-secure cloud infrastructure for data dissemination
and processing for C-sUAS protection of Presidential aviation assets.
FY 2027 Plans:
- Will continue to update Medusa Command and Control (C2) software to further interoperability and incorporation within the
Advanced Battle Management System (ABMS) architecture (e.g., Unified Data Library).
- Will continue electronic warfare upgrades, to include but not limited to new sensor and effector components, and new Ninja skills
which leverage full Ninja capability within Medusa C2 and other C2 systems.
- Will continue efforts in alignment with the DoW's JIATF.
- Will continue to evaluate new capabilities.
- Will continue to develop and test C2 capabilities, via planned incremental software sprints, bi-annual software upgrades.
- Will continue to ensure cyber security requirements are developed and incorporated in all new system changes.
- Will continue to support oversight, management, and execution of JIATF funded development efforts.
- Will continue to conduct studies, analysis, and evaluations of threats and capability gaps to refine and update requirements
enabling upgraded and improved capabilities.
- Will initiate and continue contractor testing of developed updates.
- Will integrate initial kinetic effectors for evaluation for broader DAF employment to include low collateral effects intercept (LCEI)
capabilities and other kinetic solutions such as APKWS.
- Will continue to integrate capabilities on expeditionary systems.
- Will continue to develop NCR COP technical solutions in coordination with the Air Force Rapid Capabilities Office to include joint
interoperability of Counter-small Unmanned Aircraft Systems (C-sUAS) sensors, development of correlation and fusion process,
and developing cyber-secure cloud infrastructure for data dissemination and processing for C-sUAS protection of Presidential
aviation assets.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                  FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
FY26 to FY27 increased due to NCR software and hardware development requirements.
Title: ABADS Missile Defense (MD)                                                                                                       4.085       5.749         56.106
Description: During this program phase, the ABADS MD capability will focus on integration activities, with a focus on
continued NKE integration and the introduction of kinetic and additional non-kinetic effector solutions and active defense radars.
Specifically, integration activities will leverage previous work accomplished utilizing Integrated Battle Command System and UCI
interface management to rapidly incorporate additional subsystem combat capabilities to defend Joint or Coalition bases and
critical infrastructure. RDT&E activities in this phase continue to focus on a government DevSecOps software development and
production framework, alignment with ABMS infrastructure and capabilities and incorporation of additional capabilities.

FY 2026 Plans:
- Participate in select Department of the Air Force and theater exercises and demonstrations
- Support fielding of ABADS Missile Defense (MD) capability
- Test, and field capability enhancements as identified
- Generate formal program documentation in support of fielding effort
- Develop and demonstrate a prototype Dynamic Detection Radar System (DDRS) capability including:
-- Integrate passive RF sensing with existing tactical radar systems
-- Develop multi-static coordination and communication architecture
-- Develop software for sensor fusion, target cueing, and autonomous operation
-- Conduct lab and field testing to validate performance and survivability
-- Conduct operational experimentation with USAFE-AFAFRICA.
FY 2027 Plans:
- Will continue operationalization, testing, and ultimately fielding of the Non-Kinetic Effector.
- Will participate in select DAF and theater exercises and demonstrations in support of INDOPACOM and NORTHCOM
- Will continue software development efforts on a government-run DevSecOps software pipeline
-- Will integrate and develop kinetic and additional non-kinetic effector solutions
- Will integrate and develop active defense radar solutions
- Will support oversite, management, and execution of site stand-up, fielding, and sustainment of ABADS MD in INDOPACOM,
NORTHCOM, and EUCOM
- Will develop, test, and field capability enhancements
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:

