E. Acquisition Strategy
For 2027, ABADS Missile Defense (MD) will be fully executing two Rapid Prototyping and one Rapid Fielding Middle Tier of Acquisitions (MTAs). The primary efforts
will continue the maturation of the Non-Kinetic Effector (NKE) both from a software and hardware perspective. Software initiatives will utilize a variety of contracts to
build upon fielded capability. Hardware initiatives will build upon contracts awarded in 2026 to optimize system configuration for a production cut-in aimed at reducing
production lead times by 50%. ABADS MD will continue to mature its usage of the Government Development Security Operations (DevSecOps) software pipeline for
software production and configuration management. ABADS MD will also support theater specific testing/demonstrations to mature interconnectivity and concepts of
operations.

 Additionally, ABADS MD utilize Requests for Information and a mix of sole source and competitively awarded contracts to identify, select, develop, integrate, and test
 kinetic and additional non-kinetic effector solutions and active defense radars into the ABADS MD baseline program. These activities will leverage existing design
 interface standards utilized by the program to date in order to rapidly on-board, integrate, and test the additional subsystems. The activities will also leverage existing
 software pipeline capabilities as well as DT/OT test organizations/infrastructure.

 The Advanced Battle Management System (ABMS) Division within PEO Command, Control, Communications and Battle Management (C3BM) provides contracting,
 legal, comptroller, programmatic, engineering, test, and logistics support. AFLCMC provides Other Transaction Authority.

 Counter-small Unmanned Aircraft Systems (C-sUAS) follows a MTA approach to rapidly prototype capabilities. The Government Team is augmented by Engineering
 and Integration (E&I) contract service support in an effort to keep pace with the adversary threat environment. For FY2027, the primary efforts endeavor to improve

