Effective FY 2027, activities associated with Re-entry Aerothermal Science (RAS) will be transferred to the Nuclear Re-
entry Systems Science and Technology (S&T) effort aiding enhanced terminal performance research and development
supplementing efforts within PE 0603273F, S&T for Nuclear Re-entry Systems. There will be no reallocation of funding from
Nuclear Technologies to the Nuclear Re-entry Systems S&T effort. Funding previously allocated for RAS within the Nuclear
Technologies effort will be redirected to support Nuclear Explosion Monitoring (NEM) activities enabling the expansion of
monitoring capabilities for the detection and tracking of multi-domain moving target indicators.

RAS activities will provide enhanced nuclear re-entry system aerothermodynamic analyses supporting experimentation and
modernization of nuclear re-entry system components and technologies.

