informing developmental efforts performed within PE 0603273F, S&T for Nuclear Re-entry Systems. This growth in budget will
ensure S&T for Nuclear Re-entry Systems remains on schedule with the joint Department of the Air Force (DAF) and U.S. Navy
25-year roadmap established in accordance with strategic guidance provided by the Office of the Undersecretary of War (OUSW)
for Research and Engineering (R&E) in FY 2023. The funding will support studies and early development of Aeroshell material
options for future re-entry vehicles; evaluation of materials performance in relevant environments; and the initiation of terminal
performance studies informing future re-entry vehicle design.
