       Change Summary Explanation
       Decrease in FY 2025 funding of $5.540 million in Other Adjustment was for realignment of funds to PE 0602212F, Defense Laboratories R&D Projects, to
       implement the Department of War (DoW) Funding Laboratory Enhancements Across Four Categories (FLEX-4) authority under 10 U.S.C. Section 4123.

       The FY 2026 President's Budget submittal did not reflect FY 2027 through FY 2030 funding. Therefore, an explanation of the change between the two budget
       positions for FY 2027 cannot be made in a relevant manner.

       FY 2027 increased compared to FY 2026 by $5.713 million for technology investment to develop advanced sensor technologies including radomes, apertures,
       radar seekers, automatic target recognition, and infrared/spectral Light Detection and Ranging (LiDAR) seekers; demonstrate non-global positioning system
       (GPS) navigation, develop networked weapon autonomy software/hardware architecture, and interoperability standards for weapon swarms; advance multi-
       weapon collaborative guidance via a testbed, virtual tool integration, processing pipelines, alternative computing, and artificial intelligence/machine learning (AI/
       ML) implementation in hardware-in-the-loop testing.




