Title: F-35 Integration                                                                                                                  34.463      28.393        48.876
Description: Integration of the AARGM-ER and SiAW missiles onto the F-35. Efforts for aircraft integration will address the F-35
aircraft software development, Mission Planning and Mission Data capability, engineering to support weapon integration, testing,
and airworthiness certification for the missile carriage and employment efforts.

FY 2026 Plans:
Continued integration of AARGM-ER on the F-35 as an interim combat capability, including ground testing, F-35 operational flight
program (OFP) integration, launcher adapter development, mission planning, and flight testing. Began initial integration of the
SiAW missile on the F-35, including execution of System Requirements Review to define requirements for and begin mission
planning, mission data development, ground testing, and airworthiness activities, and began establishing a System Integration Lab
(SIL).
FY 2027 Plans:
Continue integration of SiAW missile on the F-35 to include: mission planning, establishing a hardware/software lab to develop,
test and program mission data files; begin SIL testing with the aircraft platform; continue required ground tests (i.e. wind tunnel

