- Continue conducting lethality analysis and ground tests to enable design of small form factor warheads that create tradespace
for other weapon components, enabling larger solid rocket motors for increased range.
- Continue transitioning advanced target models to other AF and DoW offices to improve joint used target models.
- Continue developing preliminary design of air-to-air weapon concepts for sixth- generation platforms, maturing and
demonstrating missile component technologies to increase range and agility.
- Continue exploring and documenting missile flight dynamics trade space, focusing on maturing and demonstrating missile
component technologies to increase range, loadout, lethality, and agility.
- Continue conducting wind-tunnel experiments to characterize airframes and validate aerodynamic codes leading to development
of highly maneuverable and efficient missiles to counter advanced targets and improve persistence and survivability of future
platforms, enabling air-to-air engagements against highly maneuverable and evasive targets to employ fewer weapons per sortie.
- Continue performing experiments with small warheads to obtain data for lethality analysis to validate and improve designs,
focusing on maturing and demonstrating missile component technology to increase lethality.
- Continue planning and executing integrated sub-system experiments, focusing on maturing and demonstrating missile
component technologies to increase range, loadout, lethality, and agility.
- Continue modeling, simulation, analysis, and digital engineering in support of air-to-air advanced weapon technologies, focusing
on maturing and demonstrating missile component technologies to increase range, loadout, lethality, and agility.
- Stop conducting ground and arena tests of advanced weapons experimental carriages for sixth-generation weapon concept and
prepare for flight worthiness testing, focusing on maturing and demonstrating missile component technologies to increase loadout.
