       Change Summary Explanation
       The FY 2026 President’s Budget submission did not include FY 2027 funding projections. Therefore, no comparison between budget positions is available for
       FY 2027. The slight decrease from FY 2026 to FY 2027 is largely the result of efficiencies due to improved transparency of training information from leveraging
       Defense Security Assistance Management System training data into various modules within the Socium. Defense Security Cooperation Agency continues
       development in support of International Security Cooperation Programs authorities and of Section 333 execution management and oversight, performance
       measurements to improve visibility into building partner capacity programs, and enhancements to expand the assessment, monitoring, and evaluation framework.
       This includes structured pre-design Significant Security Cooperation Initiatives and capability assessment features. Socium will reduce duplicative data entry.
       Socium will manage comprehensive and accessible information that enhances oversight and data-driven decision-making capability, and assessment, monitoring
       and evaluation requirements.




