B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                   FY 2025       FY 2026       FY 2027
Title: Global Theater Security Cooperation Management Information System (G-TSCMIS)                                                       8.338         6.056         6.010
FY 2026 Plans:
In FY 2026, DSCA plans to continue capability and functional enhancements to Socium including authority-specific congressional
reports, expanded partner nation organization information, social network analysis, tranche analytics, improved training and
equipment list features, Resource Allocation Plan automation, integrated chat functionality, and persistent interfaces with
authoritative data source and geospatial information systems to further integrate security cooperation planning, budgeting,
resourcing, assessment, monitoring, and evaluation.
FY 2027 Plans:
As a system, Socium adapts to changes in authorities, maintains features and capabilities, and provides the centralization users
require to meet expectations. However, Socium is slated for operation and sustainment in FY 2028. Our goal is to complete the
development required to meet any mandated requirements for the system, and over the FY 2027-2028 timeframe, gradually move
to a focus on operation and sustainment. Operations and Maintenance funding would be used to help troubleshoot updates, minor
enhancements, and bugs fixes to ensure the features and functions already developed remain in effective operation. Additionally,
this will allow one team to focus on the Operations and Maintenance support and one to focus on completing the development
support, effectively freeing up the agile pipeline to flow more easily.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
The decrease in FY 2026 to FY 2027 is largely due to improved transparency of training information, leveraging Defense Security
Assistance Management System training data into various modules within the Socium.
