Remarks

D. Acquisition Strategy
DSCA worked closely with the Office of the Deputy Assistant Secretary of War for Global Partnerships to shape the guidance for the Significant Security Cooperation
Initiatives process requiring the use of Socium and continues to support the security cooperation enterprise to integrate AM&E and Defense Institution Building for all
U.S. security cooperation activities. Future enhancements through FY 2026 include tailored authority-specific analytics and reporting, enhanced AM&E features, and
continued authoritative data source integration. Following the capability and application enhancements implemented in prior years, DSCA is working closely with the
Socium user community to continue building tailored workflows in support of security cooperation partnership efforts. DSCA plans to finalize Performance Monitoring
Plan and Lessons Learned database enhancements for AM&E to improve program oversight. Strategic Planning enhancements will continue for various workflows,

