C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                    FY 2025     FY 2026       FY 2027
Title: TRANSCOM Innovation                                                                                                                 0.000       1.386         0.494
Description: Annual investment in emerging technologies to enhance the ability to globally project and sustain the joint warfighter/
address Joint Deployment and Distribution Enterprise (JDDE) and Joint Petroleum Enterprise (JPE) challenges. Includes
contribution to Small Business Innovative Research (SBIR) programs.

FY 2026 Plans:
Funds are used to support New Start research projects garnered via an annual March through October solicitation process.
Funds also used to collaboratively invest/shape in the Office of the Undersecretary of War, Research & Engineering
(OUSW(R&E)) programs (e.g., Defense Innovation Accelerator) proposals that address contested logistics challenges. On
average, this line supports the funding of approximately six New Starts per year.
FY 2027 Plans:
Same as previous years, funds are used to support New Start research projects garnered via an annual March through October
solicitation process. Funds also used to collaboratively invest/shape in the Office of the Undersecretary of War, Research
& Engineering (OUSW(R&E)) programs (e.g., Defense Innovation Accelerator) proposals that address contested logistics
challenges. On average, this line supports the funding of approximately six New Starts per year.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Decrease due to funds being applied to collaboratively funded investments in the Office of the Undersecretary of War, Research
& Engineering (OUSW(R&E)) programs (e.g., Defense Innovation Accelerator) proposals that address contested logistics
challenges. These funds help reduce duplication of effort across the Department.
Title: Modular Self Propelled Wheel Technology                                                                                                -        2.000              -
Description: Develop a lightweight, rugged, compact cargo handling vehicle to modernize expeditionary operations.

FY 2026 Plans:
Development of modular, compact vehicles equipped with self-propelled wheel to enhance ground handling and mobile platform
capabilities, making them particularly valuable for expeditionary operations.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Increase due to a one year congressional add in FY2026 with funding executed by Air Force Research Lab.
Title: Aerial Delivery and Autonomous Deployment of Unmanned Vehicles Joint Aerial Delivery Demonstration Exhibition (JADDE)               0.100       0.000          0.000
Description: This funding supports the demonstration of funded airdrop capabilities. Technical partner U.S. Army Combat
Capabilities Development Command (DEVCOM) Soldier Center.

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                  FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
FY 2026 Plans:
Funding shift to support the combined demonstration of multiple aerial delivery capabilities in an operational environment to
demonstrate capability/help facilitate transition of proven technologies.
FY 2027 Plans:
N/A.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
N/A.
Title: Contested Logistics Ops By Robots for Expeditionary Recon                                                                        0.000       1.000          1.900
Description: A versatile, high speed, utilitarian craft with deployable bow ramp capable of delivering 14K / 20K of cargo over 400
nm to the littorals/ports at 20 kts in sea state 3. Technical Partner United States Central Command (USCENTCOM). Transition
partner HQ USMC Combat Development & Integration (CD&I)/Capabilities Development Directorate (CDD).

FY 2026 Plans:
Completion & testing of Small High-speed Amphibious Role-variant Craft (SHARC) Prototype #2 (extended form factor to
accommodate TRANSCOM funded/USMC owned Automated Pallet Loader (APL); retrofit of SHARC Prototype #1 with any
equipment changes from Prototype #2 development; integration of the initial operating capability (IOC) of Government Off the
Shelf (GOTS)/Commercial Off the Shelf (COTS) networking & collaborative & autonomy SW framework into Prototypes #1 & 2;
demo craft functionality for both SHARCs plus IOC autonomy; initial Concepts of Operations (CONOPS)/Tactic Techniques and
Procedures (TTP) development in representative operational scenarios & development of key performance parameters (KPPs)
with Measures of Performance (MOPs)/Measures of Effectiveness (MOEs) for all demonstrated technologies.
FY 2027 Plans:
Integrate & test SHARCs #1 & 2 with initial operating capbility networking & autonomy hardware & software capabilities. Deliver
prototype #2 (45 ft. extended version), IOC networking & autonomy solution, and develop/provide comprehensive final report.
Technical Partner United States Central Command (USCENTCOM).
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Increase due to preparation for delivery of prototype #2 and final report development.
Title: Integrated Communications and Mission Planning for Autonomous Resupply Systems                                                   0.000       0.900          2.000
Description: Develop command & control (C2) software front-end plug-ins that will be compatible with extended range aerial
delivery vehicles, integrated Mission Planning (MP) support that is interoperable with selected C2 platform(s) to enable near
real time evaluation of mission progress leveraging vehicle performance models, airdrop models, and route optimization

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                   FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
algorithms, C2 communications hardware (non-developmental/commercial off the shelf) including ground stations, radios, and
vehicle hardware, and payload tracking, and Joint Precision Airdrop long-range software and hardware updates to support
C2 interoperability. Technical Partner: U.S. Army Capabilities Development Command. Transition to Product Manager Force
Sustainment System (PdM-FSS), USMC Combat Capabilities and Integration, Capabilities Development Division, Logistics
Combat Element and USAF MP Systems Program Office within U.S. Air Force Life Cycle Management Center Airspace Mission
Planning (AFLCMC/HBM) for integration into the Consolidated Airdrop Tool (CAT) PoR.

FY 2026 Plans:
Mission planning software required for extended range vehicles development. Interface plugin(s) for the selected C2 tool will be
developed to facilitate data exchange/transfer between Airdrop Mission Planner and the C2 tool, and between the C2 tool and the
selected vehicle platform(s). A C2 tool will be developed for integration with the mission planning software and the vehicle flight
software.
FY 2027 Plans:
The Long Range Mission Planner module, built on AMP software, will be updated to conform with an Interface Control Document
(ICD) for interoperability with C2 tool(s) and provide increased capability for rapid replanning in-flight.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Increase due to software updates that significantly increase development costs in FY2026. In addition, project starts mid-year
FY2026 and FY2027 represents a full year of execution.
Title: Integrating Space Transportation for USTRANSCOM Cargo Transport                                                                   0.000       0.711          1.575
Description: Deliver mature prototypes of designs and system-level procedures for commercial space transportation integration
with the Joint Deployment and Distribution Enterprise (JDDE). The objectives both leverage and augment the science and
technology (S&T) development of the Air Force Research Lab/U.S. Space Force Rocket Cargo Vanguard program and inform
Department investment in the use of space transportation to deliver cargo/sustainment in contested operations.

FY 2026 Plans:
Report of knowledge acquisition findings/plan of action, C2 System Operational View (OV)-1 and OV-4, regulatory compliance
mission assessment, and design factors report and network design.
FY 2027 Plans:
C2 System Prototype Design Delivered, Supply Chain Integration Model Delivered, Tabletop Exercise, Alert Level System Model
delivered.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:

C. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions)                                                                                         FY 2025    FY 2026       FY 2027
Increase due to development starts mid-year FY2026. FY2027 will see a full year of development.
Title: Rapid Aircraft Load Planner Handheld (RALPH)                                                                                            0.000       0.650          0.600
Description: Air distribution to remote, austere locations for small loads poorly suited to C-130 efficiency. Use of unmanned light
aircraft for cargo movement to the tactical edge will call for non-aerial port personnel to perform basic aircraft loading and load
planning. Employment of a customized tool supports system velocity. Project provides a unique, emerging Rapid Distribution
Technology (a JDDE challenge), that directly supports the employment of uncrewed, optionally piloted aircraft for light cargo
distribution and is particularly relevant to retrograde cargo operations. Technical partner United States Indo-Pacific Command
(USINDOPACOM). Transition strategy is to provide as an application to be loaded by user (e.g., onto pilot's electronic flight bag
 for air).

FY 2026 Plans:
Scanner functional to include weight entry and data table output, upper & lower cargo bays graphically defined (two aircraft),
graphic load planner linked to data table, graphic load planner linked to data table, and field testing complete by operational units.
FY 2027 Plans:
Continue Scanner functional to include weight entry and data table output, upper & lower cargo bays graphically defined (two
aircraft), graphic load planner linked to data table, graphic load planner linked to data table, and field testing complete by
operational units.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Decrease due to funding shifting from FY2026 to FY2027.
Title: Small Unit Resupply Decision Dominance                                                                                                  0.000       0.960          2.005
Description: An integrated and automated resupply planning and execution system that streamlines and accelerates the
responsiveness of emergency aerial resupply by minimizing human in the loop decision making. Project facilitates rapid/accurate
decision making, at the tactical edge. Technical partner U.S. Army Capabilities Development Command. Transition to U.S. Army
Program Executive Office (PEO) Soldier Project Manager Soldier Warrior (PM SWAR).

FY 2026 Plans:
Development that will first allow the sustainment support personnel to establish a vehicle inventory at the field level, capturing
information such as vehicle type, serial number, mission readiness, and location. The specific vehicle being used for a given
resupply mission will now be selectable within the mission profile, which results in the ability to monitor the fleet of resupply vehicle
availability for current and future operations.
FY 2027 Plans:

