Conduct several demonstrations where users and Test and Evaluation personnel can assess the technologies suitability and
effectiveness. These Soldier touch points and capability testing will be completed along, and in addition to, platform testing
incrementally showing more features as programs progress.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Increase due to project development beginning mid-year FY2026. FY2027 represents a full year of development.
Title: Synthetic Data Generation Engine                                                                                                      0.000       0.614          0.362
Description: Developing a capability to rapidly generate unclassified data that has a similar structure to existing classified data
sets within the command. This automatic data generation framework will allow for the creation of large, synthetic data sets that
can be used for a variety of purposes, including training exercises, system testing, and other activities that require data that is not
necessarily identical to current operational data. Technical lead is USTRANSCOM J6. Transition as enterprise-wide capability
useable by multiple Programs Of Record (PORs) or by a single POR dedicated to the creation of synthetic data for mission
partners.

FY 2026 Plans:
Identify and document a detailed data-driven use case that could benefit from synthetic data generation, collect and analyze real
data (if available) to understand characteristics and underlying patterns, document potential techniques and tools for synthetic
data generation.
FY 2027 Plans:
Contiune to develop an initial prototype focusing on simple synthetic data generation techniques.
FY 2026 to FY 2027 Increase/Decrease Statement:
Funding decrease due to partial funding shifted to FY2027.
Title: Logistics Insights Networking and Collaboration (LINC)                                                                                0.000       0.700          1.080
Description: Demonstrate a proof-of-concept architecture facilitating end-to-end bi-directional linkages between selected tactical
and operational tools. This approach ensures end users retain access to tools tailored to their needs while benefitting from the
cumulative wisdom of networked tools. Technical partner United States Marine Corps. This transition would provide the USMC,
Navy, Army and users in the special operations community with shared access to logistics and sustainment analytic tools that
integrate commercial and DoW data and offer near real time monitoring of key nodes, dependencies and resources.

FY 2026 Plans:

